<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-17T20:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-17T20:41:00-05:00" n="1255" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1255">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/400.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-17T19:00:00-06:41">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring my August 15. Nafarrate has referred matter of war contribution
                            to Governor Caballero and will take no further action relative to
                            collection same pending instructions from his superior officer.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>